g.text: Due to the mess that this 70+ class class diagram is going to be, I declare a couple custom
stereotypes and somewhat "rules" to make it managable.
1. «get/set» or just «get» or «set» streotypes mean that the field has a public getter/setter.
2. «reference» stereotype to refer to an already existing classifier (class/interface/enum)
3. «throws» dependency stereotype for custom exception throw
Not every dependency is going to be explicitly stated. I try my best but most dependencies will
still be implicitly inherited from the one they already have.
As an example depending on a class automatically makes that class's field type be depended
Writing these out would require me to formalize this, which I don't have the bain power to do.
I'm not going to be the one making UML usable.
